Number of BST From Array

You are given an integer array arr[] containing distinct elements.

Your task is to return an array where the ith element denotes the number of unique BSTs formed when arr[i] is chosen as the root.

Examples :

Input: arr[] = [2, 1, 3]
Output: [1, 2, 2]
Explanation: 
4
Input: arr[] = [2, 1]
Ouput: [1, 1]
Constraints:
1 ≤ arr.size() ≤ 6
1 ≤ arr[i] ≤ 15

Expected Complexities
Time Complexity: O(n log n)
Auxiliary Space: O(n)


JAVA-
class Solution {
    public ArrayList<Integer> countBSTs(int[] arr) {
      ArrayList<Integer> ans = new ArrayList<>();
       int n = arr.length;
      int dummy[] = new int[arr.length];
      int[] catalan = {1, 1, 2, 5, 14, 42, 132};
      for(int i = 0;i < n;i++)
      {
          dummy[i] = arr[i];
      }
      Arrays.sort(dummy);
     
      for(int i = 0;i < n;i++)
      {
          for(int j = 0;j < n;j++)
          {
             if(arr[i] == dummy[j])
             {
                 int left = j;
                 int right = n - j - 1;
                 int num = catalan[left] * catalan[right];
                 ans.add(num);
                 break;
             }
          }
      }
      return ans;
    }
}
